This branch contains Containerfile for building the container with the TeamSpeak 3 server

============================================
# HOW TO PREPARE THE CONSTAINER FOR PRODUCTION

podman build -f containerfile
podman run --network host -ti <hash_of_the_BUILT_container>

# IN PARALLEL
| podman exec -ti <hash_of_the_RUNNING_container> bash
|	nano ../TS3_SERVER_SECRETS
|
| podman commit <hash_of_the_RUNNING_container> 
| podman tag <new_hash> teamspeak3_server

---

# At this point, the server will autostart upon the container execution
# Run with:
podman run --network host -d <hash_of_the_TAGGED_image>

============================================
# GENERAL HELP

Build with:
  podman build -f containerfile

Tag the image (assign name to it):
  podman tag <hash> <name>

Run container with:
  podman run --network host -d <hash>

Attach to the conatiner (to the TS server output) with:
  podman attach <hash>

Connect to the conatiner independently why it runs:
  podman exec -ti <hash> bash

============================================
